.MARINE...
(Today through Monday)
Issued at 503 AM PDT Wed Apr 1 2026

A passing cold front today and tonight will bring unsettled
weather and stronger winds. A fresh to moderate breeze will
develop through the day north of Pigeon Point initially before
spread south tonight. Strong northerly breezes will develop by
Thursday afternoon and persist through Friday with moderate seas
building to become rough with widespread hazardous conditions.
Winds and seas ease Friday night and over the weekend.

